Description:
['About this space', "Waking up to the splashing of rainbow trout and the music of the hermit thrush as you gaze out on the pristine pond at Moose Meadow. The Treehouse is where nature and luxury come together in tranquil harmony, and where your imagination can soar. It's a perfect location to isolate yourself with your loved one, away from others.", 'The space', 'The space
This New England Treehouse features a living & dining area on the first floor with an expansive wrap-around deck. Enjoy the view of the woods as you climb up the circular staircase wrapped around a maple tree. The second-story bedroom with its custom made queen size bed provides comfort and warmth, while the balcony provides a high perch to take in the surrounding natural beauty.', 'Guest access', "Guest access
The Treehouse is part of the Moose Meadow Lodge Bed & Breakfast. Treehouse guests will be given a full breakfast each morning and will also have access to the lodge's kitchen for storing food, and for preparing snacks or meals. A variety of restaurants are nearby for lunch or dinner.", 'Other things to note', "Other things to note
We are a lodging facility that is licensed, inspected and registered with the VT Department of Health. We are also members of the Vermont Chamber of Commerce, Mad River Valley Chamber of Commerce and Revitalizing Waterbury.

COVID-19: Due to the rise in COVID-19 infections, we require proof of vaccination for those age 5 or older or proof of a negative COVID test (antigen or PCR) within 24 hours prior to arrival. Masks are required in public spaces in the presence of people outside your household. If you're feeling any COVID-19 symptoms, stay home. You will not be allowed to enter. We appreciate your help in mitigating the pandemic and look forward to welcoming you.

If you or anyone in your party has had any symptoms within the last 24 hours, stay home. You will not be allowed to enter. Symptoms include:
